Here is a clean, production-ready implementation of **REST API pagination logic (variant 14)** in Api.

### Explanation
Implements cursor-based pagination for robust, fast result fetches. Specifically, this handles variant case 14.

### Implementation
```javascript
app.get('/items_v14', async (req, res) => {
  const limit = parseInt(req.query.limit) || 10;
  const cursor = req.query.cursor;
  const items = await db.items.findMany({
    take: limit,
    skip: cursor ? 1 : 0,
    cursor: cursor ? { id: cursor } : undefined,
    orderBy: { id: 'asc' }
  });
  res.json({ data: items, nextCursor: items[items.length - 1]?.id });
});
```

